  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (c5791f5 2022-11-11T00:05:26.949466Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThe script would exit with the following error code when switching to the second network and repeat the deployment process. \r\n\r\n- I used start/stop broadcast\r\n- I would call vm.stopBroadcast() and then vm.createSelectFork()\r\n- when I changed from vm.createSelect() to creating both forks at the start of the script and them simply selecting them, the error did not surface\r\n- I used slow and without slow (same result)\r\n- I changed the forked networks and it was always the second network, even if it was the same two networks but in a different deployment order\r\n- The networks were anvil instances in forking mode\r\n\r\n```\r\n==========================\r\n\r\nONCHAIN EXECUTION COMPLETE & SUCCESSFUL.\r\nTotal Paid: 0.052385907 ETH (17461969 gas * avg 3 gwei)\r\n\r\n###\r\nFinding wallets for all the necessary addresses...\r\n##\r\nSending transactions [0 - 11].\r\n\r\nTransactions saved to: /Users/odysseas/code/nomad/monorepo/broadcast/multi/DeployImplementations.s.sol-latest/deploy.json\r\n\r\nError:\r\n[Err(\r\nEOA nonce changed unexpectedly while sending transactions.)]\r\nTime: 0h:00m:01s\r\n```",
